# Button render (layout builder)

Read `.cursor/AGENTS.md` and `skills/generate-button-json/SKILL.md` before generating or editing button JSON.

## JSON rules

- **Required**: `type: "button"`, `id` (unique string), and either `label` (string) or non-empty `children`.
- **Discriminant**: `type` must be exactly `"button"` (lowercase).
- **Variants**: `default` | `destructive` | `outline` | `secondary` | `ghost` | `link` — match shadcn Button.
- **Sizes**: `default` | `sm` | `lg` | `icon` — match `ButtonItem` in `types.ts` (UI may support extra sizes; stick to these for layout JSON).
- **HTML type**: use `buttonType` (`submit` | `button` | `reset`), not `type`, for the native button element.
- **Actions**: `action` (event name string) + optional `actionParams` (object). Handler wiring is app-level via `LayoutBuilder` `onAction` (planned).
- **Condition**: optional `condition` string evaluated against `LayoutBuilder` `data` (e.g. `"data.canSubmit === true"`).
- **Children vs label**: if `children.length > 0`, renderer shows children and ignores `label`.

## Renderer rules

- Map props via spread to `@workspace/ui/components/button`; do not invent new JSON fields without updating `types.ts` and this doc.
- `icon` / `iconPosition` are declared in `types.ts` but not yet rendered in `index.tsx` — do not generate icon JSON until implemented.
- Keep `action` / `actionParams` destructured even if click handler is not wired yet.

## Validation checklist

```
- [ ] type === "button"
- [ ] id is unique within the layout tree
- [ ] label or children present
- [ ] variant/size enums valid
- [ ] buttonType set for form submit buttons
- [ ] JSON is strict (no comments, no trailing commas)
```
